---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';

const description = "Debt collector letter — 'Here's how to contact me.' Restrict how and when a debt collector can contact you under federal law (FDCPA).";
---

<Base title="Debt Collector: Restricted Contact Letter — CreditCookbook" description={description} posterTitle="RESTRICTED CONTACT" posterLabel="// debt collector response template">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label" data-animate>// debt collector response — restricted contact</span>
      <h2 data-animate style="margin-bottom: 16px;">"Here's How To Contact Me"</h2>
      <p data-animate style="max-width: 60ch; margin-bottom: 32px; opacity: 0.7;">Use this letter to tell a debt collector how they may contact you and to instruct them not to contact you any other way. Under federal law, debt collectors can't contact you at a time or place they know is inconvenient. They also can't contact you at work if you tell them your employer prohibits it. Be careful not to over-restrict — if you want to work something out, you don't want to make it too hard for them to reach you.</p>

      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 48px;" data-animate>
        <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="navigator.clipboard.writeText(document.getElementById('letter').textContent)">Copy letter</button>
        <a href="/recipes/dispute-letters" class="btn btn-ghost">Back to dispute letters</a>
      </div>

      <div id="letter" class="mono-block" style="margin-bottom: 48px;" data-animate>
[YOUR NAME]
[YOUR RETURN ADDRESS]
[DATE]

[DEBT COLLECTOR NAME]
[DEBT COLLECTOR ADDRESS]

Re: [ACCOUNT NUMBER FOR THE DEBT, IF YOU HAVE IT]

Dear debt collector:

I am responding to your contact about collecting a debt.
You contacted me by [PHONE/MAIL], on [DATE] and identified
the debt as [ANY INFORMATION THEY GAVE YOU ABOUT THE DEBT].

You can contact me about this debt, but only in the way I
say below. Don't contact me about this debt in any other
way, or at any other place or time. It is inconvenient to
me to be contacted except as I authorize below.

You can only contact me at:

Mailing address: [MAILING ADDRESS IF YOU WANT TO GET MAIL]
Phone: [PHONE NUMBER AND CONVENIENT TIMES]

[IF CORRECT, INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING:]
My employer prohibits me from receiving communications like
this at work.

Thank you for your cooperation.

Sincerely,

[YOUR NAME]
      </div>

      <div class="card" data-animate>
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Sending instructions</h4>
        <ul style="margin-left: 24px; line-height: 2;">
          <li>Fill in your information on the template and edit as needed</li>
          <li>Specify exactly how and when you can be contacted</li>
          <li>Include the work restriction paragraph only if your employer prohibits such communications</li>
          <li>Print and send the letter — keep a copy for your records</li>
          <li>Send via certified mail with return receipt</li>
          <li>Stopping a collector from calling doesn't cancel the debt — you could still be sued</li>
          <li>In some cases, phone calls are the best way to deal with a debt collector</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "HowTo",
    "name": "Debt Collector Restricted Contact Letter",
    "description": "Letter to restrict how and when a debt collector may contact you under the FDCPA.",
    "totalTime": "PT10M",
    "step": [
      {"@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Fill in your information", "text": "Complete your name, return address, and the date at the top of the letter."},
      {"@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Add debt collector details", "text": "Fill in the debt collector's name, address, and the account number if you have it."},
      {"@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Specify contact methods", "text": "List the mailing address and phone number with convenient times where you can be reached. Delete any methods you don't want to allow."},
      {"@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Consider work restriction", "text": "Include the paragraph about employer prohibition only if it applies to your situation."},
      {"@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Print and mail", "text": "Print the letter and mail it via certified mail with return receipt. Keep a copy for your records."}
    ]
  })} />
</Base>
